title: Warm Starry Night
overview: Lew, a famous model, struggles with amnesia following a suicide attempt brought on by heartbreak. Determined to recover her lost memories of the man she loved, she seeks solace in Chiang Khan, a tranquil Thai town where she once worked with Traipob. Pawat, a piano teacher nursing his own heartache, finds refuge in the same town. They both check into a homestay called "Lom Nao Dao Oun" and, despite initial conflicts, gradually develop feelings for each other. However, Lew's forgotten boyfriend and her mysterious nightmares complicate their journey to uncover the truth.
